item.dc:creator: sersoft
item.description:
Hey! I have the handwriting of an 8 yr old, but I used to write perfectly with an ink pen, my handwriting was the best in school, people thought it was printed because it was always perfect.

I forgot how to write properly because I started learning English and French at the same time, and then discovered the Internet, now my handwriting looks just like this font.

item.title: Gordon attempting to find work after resonance cascade
item.dc:creator: samzala
item.description:
DinoThrasher:

For a theoretical physicist, his hand writing could use some work.
His self-portrait on the other hand is surprisingly well done for someone who can barely write.

The quality of your handwriting isn’t exactly connected to your drawing skills. My handwriting is God awful and yet I can draw rather well. :rolleyes: And how does the looks of someones handwriting exactly determine how intelligent or capable he is? The smartest mathematician in our class has the handwriting of an 8 year old.
